This is the **right question** â€” it goes to the heart of **why decision- & data-driven CLM works** and **why Case Types should remain unchanged**.

Short answer:

> **You can add a new task for an EMEA country WITHOUT changing the Case Type**
> **if (and only if) tasks are generated via decisions + data**.

Below is the **exact, concrete pattern** to do this correctly in Pega.

---

# Target principle (non-negotiable)

> **Case Type defines stages, not tasks**
> **Tasks are data-driven artifacts created at runtime**

So:

* âŒ Do **not** add tasks directly in Case Type
* âŒ Do **not** add new assignments in flows per country
* âœ… Add tasks via **decision + data**

---

